13410 (BR, ORT). https://observation.org/observation/205255016/
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E18BBCB1562463FB5BC00DB6573EECB" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" type="notes">
<paragraph id="782DD2DDE9F8D8171A02872C9AFD4BAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="63BB0EE6509E4E06B3184E7FC55AAE19" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">
This New World weed is increasingly naturalised in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="A20A6554B5C06552800F3556FB3C5DDE" author="Martini, F" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" pagination="59 - 63" refId="B6509265" refString="Martini, F, Scholz, H, 1998. Eragrostis virescens J. Presl (Poaceae), a new alien species for the Italian flora. Willdenowia 28: 59 - 63" title="Eragrostis virescens J. Presl (Poaceae), a new alien species for the Italian flora" volume="28" year="1998">Martini and Scholz 1998</bibRefCitation>
). In the Canary Islands, it was first reported from La Palma (
<bibRefCitation id="F2813A97DD830D73F6186894F2335EE8" author="Otto, R" journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" pagination="491 - 496" refId="B6509379" refString="Otto, R, Scholz, H, Scholz, S, 2008. Supplements to the flora of the Canary Islands, Spain: Poaceae. Willdenowia 38: 491 - 496" title="Supplements to the flora of the Canary Islands, Spain: Poaceae" volume="38" year="2008">Otto et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Since 2012, it is also known from two localities in Gran Canaria (
<bibRefCitation id="6D0FB438EBB3C3C14304955C92A83A07" author="Marrero Rodriguez, A" journalOrPublisher="Botanica Macaronesica" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" pagination="121 - 142" refId="B6509247" refString="Marrero Rodriguez, A, 2019. Adiciones corologicas a la flora vascular de gran canaria, especies xenofitas, ocasionales o potenciales invasoras. Botanica Macaronesica 30: 121 - 142" title="Adiciones corologicas a la flora vascular de gran canaria, especies xenofitas, ocasionales o potenciales invasoras" volume="30" year="2019">
Marrero 
<normalizedToken id="0B35FF7C2CFA237D71E417A7FAB9FCBE" originalValue="Rodríguez">Rodriguez</normalizedToken>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). In December 2018, 
<taxonomicName id="0F9A6F2C8F96A13A47AA47D18A2B97CC" authorityName="J. Presl" authorityYear="1830" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eragrostis virescens" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis id="AF31CDF1A75AC1150836579B9DDD6B46" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">Eragrostis virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed in relative abundance along dirt tracks in Santa 
<normalizedToken id="479AF141853A964C1CCBF791B36606A1" originalValue="Úrsula">Ursula</normalizedToken>
, for the first time in Tenerife.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="24AB74BE6A6E3234E5843207C1334A8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="62878">This species looks fully naturalised. A further spread in similar habitats in the area can be expected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
